{
  "stem": "23428.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But as it turns out, the fact that this two-page document existed really was very useful later, because that meant that the SS had a file called Andreas Chrambach.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And whenever you had a file, I think people were lots more careful not to let you disappear silently, as they could if the-- later in concentration camp, if there was no way to trace your existence.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So-- so I think I owe to that-- to that phony file the fact that when I finally arrived in Auschwitz, I was given, like everybody else, an identifying mark, which was-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] which was the-- the Jewish star.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was one yellow triangle superimposed on a red triangle.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And red triangles were-- were the mark for political prisoners.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So it made you what was called in the camp a political Jew, which-- which meant, as I just said, that-- that your chances of survival, at times, were probably better than if you were an unidentified-- unidentifiable transport Jude, transport Jew, as they were called, in the camp, who had no records whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Something like six weeks.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing, apart from cleaning the floors outside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I should say, sometimes, the floors had to be cleaned with toothbrushes, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] just to annoy us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we didn't care, because it took just longer time and we had more time to breathe fresh air.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There was absolutely no-- no activity other than sitting, praying, watching.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You could-- could hardly move.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My brother and I were culturally and ethnically and so much out-- out of phase with everybody else.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We really didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, I remember one guy I was impressed with.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
